WEBVTT

00:03.333 --> 00:04.542
SAM:
<i>Signposts.</i>

00:04.542 --> 00:07.417
<i>They say, very clearly, "You are here,"</i>

00:07.417 --> 00:09.500
<i>even if "here"</i>
<i>isn't where you wanna be,</i>

00:09.500 --> 00:14.375
<i>and especially when, inevitably,</i>
<i>the billionaire you let get away shows up.</i>

00:14.375 --> 00:15.458
Hello, Sam.

00:16.291 --> 00:19.125
Funk. Hi.

00:19.125 --> 00:23.166
It was so weird. I was just walking by,
and I found this arrow.

00:23.166 --> 00:26.834
So things are going well for you
since you left my company?

00:27.291 --> 00:29.417
Yeah, super-duper. Yeah.

00:29.417 --> 00:33.542
No, I mean, I get to work outdoors,
you know?

00:33.542 --> 00:36.834
Not all cooped up in some limo.

00:37.458 --> 00:41.333
You know, it is so good to see you.
I'm glad I didn't take the helicopter.

00:41.333 --> 00:43.875
Heh. Probably still could have seen me.

00:43.875 --> 00:46.041
You can probably see me from space.

00:46.041 --> 00:47.333
Well, I'll let you know.

00:47.333 --> 00:50.625
I'm actually gonna be hitching a ride
on the shuttle in June.

00:50.625 --> 00:51.959
Really?

00:51.959 --> 00:54.834
Oh, eating meals through a tube.

00:54.834 --> 00:56.667
No, thank you.

00:56.667 --> 00:57.959
You take care, Sam.

00:57.959 --> 01:01.000
- And say hi to your mom for me, all right?
- Yeah.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.333
[SOFTLY]
Bye.

01:10.458 --> 01:11.917
- Hey.
- Whew.

01:12.417 --> 01:13.750
Hey.

01:13.750 --> 01:16.834
You're making it look like you made food.
Who are you apologizing to?

01:16.834 --> 01:20.417
Well, my mother is coming over here
to discuss our business,

01:20.417 --> 01:23.291
and I am going to quit.

01:24.083 --> 01:25.834
[WHISPERS] Yeah.
- Oh.

01:26.083 --> 01:27.667
Okay, so I'm just gonna go.

01:27.667 --> 01:29.041
She'll understand, right?

01:29.041 --> 01:30.250
I mean, she has to.

01:30.250 --> 01:32.166
I just can't do it anymore.

01:32.166 --> 01:33.750
How did I get here, you know?

01:33.750 --> 01:37.500
I mean, a year ago, I make this big old
deal about leaving Chapman and Funk

01:37.500 --> 01:39.959
to go do great things with my life,

01:39.959 --> 01:43.959
and now, here I am, working
with my mother in this dead-end job.

01:43.959 --> 01:46.792
And my ex-boyfriend's sleeping
on my couch because I need the rent.

01:46.792 --> 01:49.417
I mean, is that not the lamest thing
you've ever heard?

01:50.542 --> 01:52.458
Well, it's up there, but no.

01:52.458 --> 01:54.792
I just have to do something,
I have to do anything.

01:54.792 --> 01:57.291
God, it was so obvious
when I was talking to Funk today.

01:57.291 --> 02:01.208
- Funk? Where'd you see Funk?
- Oh, on the street corner that I work.

02:01.208 --> 02:02.625
That didn't come out right.

02:02.625 --> 02:07.208
- Anyway, he's sitting there in his limo--
- A "limo." Ha-ha-ha.

02:07.208 --> 02:08.959
I bet he looked like a dork.

02:08.959 --> 02:13.542
Yeah, he was pretty jealous
of my big arrow.

02:15.417 --> 02:16.792
[SIGHS]

02:20.750 --> 02:22.291
Andrea.

02:22.291 --> 02:24.291
- I hate to bother you.
- Then don't.

02:24.291 --> 02:27.041
Oh. Heh-heh. That's funny.

02:27.041 --> 02:32.000
The school I'm substitute-teaching
at is having a fundraiser auction.

02:32.000 --> 02:34.250
- You're a teacher?
- You knew that.

02:34.709 --> 02:38.041
- What happened to that flower shop?
- I've never had a flower shop.

02:38.041 --> 02:40.959
Mm. I guess we'll have to agree
to disagree, then.

02:40.959 --> 02:43.250
Okay, yeah.

02:43.250 --> 02:46.250
Anyway, I was thinking,

02:46.250 --> 02:50.750
maybe if I donated a ball
autographed by Tony Dane,

02:50.750 --> 02:53.792
that maybe the school
would hire me full-time,

02:53.792 --> 02:56.458
and then I'd get that insurance. Yay.

02:57.750 --> 03:00.500
Since when am I someone
you can ask for a favor?

03:00.500 --> 03:03.125
Since I Heimliched that olive
out of your throat.

03:03.125 --> 03:04.625
Some favor. That was my dinner.

03:04.625 --> 03:06.709
Look, Andrea, I need that dental.

03:06.709 --> 03:11.125
I keep trying to chew every bite 20 times
like I promised my mom,

03:11.125 --> 03:14.333
but I get to, like,
14 and I just taste blood.

03:14.333 --> 03:15.834
Listen to what I'm dealing with.

03:15.834 --> 03:18.208
According to research
from Tony Dane's publicist,

03:18.208 --> 03:19.500
people think I'm heartless.

03:19.500 --> 03:22.792
Wow, I don't know
where they're getting that. I mean, that's--

03:22.792 --> 03:26.458
Six out of ten people surveyed
would rather see Tony gay than marry me.

03:26.458 --> 03:29.500
If I don't start testing better,
they're gonna call off my wedding.

03:29.500 --> 03:35.166
Hey, huh?
What if you get this ball signed for me,

03:35.166 --> 03:38.166
and then people won't think
you're as horrible as you really are?

03:39.834 --> 03:41.750
Better idea.

03:41.750 --> 03:45.834
I'll get that ball signed for you, but first,

03:45.834 --> 03:47.458
how do you feel about choking to death?

03:48.083 --> 03:49.417
Oh.

03:49.917 --> 03:52.291
I don't know.
I always thought I'd be stabbed.

03:52.750 --> 03:55.000
I have always envied this
about you, Samantha.

03:55.000 --> 03:58.083
I can never relax in my home
unless it's clean.

03:58.959 --> 04:00.250
Yeah.

04:00.250 --> 04:02.125
Sit down, Mom. Um...

04:03.875 --> 04:05.500
Pizza bagel?

04:05.500 --> 04:07.375
Oh, Lord, you pretended to make food.

04:07.375 --> 04:09.333
What have you done?

04:09.625 --> 04:11.834
Okay, Mom.

04:11.834 --> 04:13.000
Now, listen.

04:13.000 --> 04:15.041
I love working with you,

04:15.041 --> 04:19.458
- but this is just not my dream job, and I--
- Don't say another word.

04:19.458 --> 04:22.125
- I understand.
- I don't think you do.

04:22.125 --> 04:25.333
- I don't feel horrible yet.
- This is not the job for you, I get that.

04:25.542 --> 04:27.625
- Oh.
- It's like when I used to help

04:27.625 --> 04:29.250
with your math homework,
and, finally,

04:29.250 --> 04:32.166
I just stopped
trying to push that rock up a hill.

04:32.166 --> 04:35.208
And I said "She's not gonna need
this math. She's pretty."

04:36.625 --> 04:38.625
That was a while ago,
but, you know, still.

04:40.250 --> 04:43.792
- You know what you need to do?
- Yes, something meaningful with my life.

04:43.792 --> 04:47.000
- Go to Vegas.
- What? Vegas? Why?

04:47.000 --> 04:49.208
I got an invitation
to a motivational seminar.

04:49.208 --> 04:52.834
They promise to focus you on your dream
and help you achieve it.

04:52.834 --> 04:54.458
Plus I got tickets to Bette Midler.

04:54.458 --> 04:57.458
Yes. Mom, that is exactly what I need.

04:57.458 --> 04:59.750
Well, except for betting
on the Midler thing,

04:59.750 --> 05:01.834
because I don't know anything
about gambling,

05:01.834 --> 05:03.458
but Vegas, yes. Let's do it!

05:15.375 --> 05:17.709
- Real estate. You tricked me.
- No, no, no.

05:17.709 --> 05:20.291
- Unbelievable!
- No, no. Not really, no.

05:20.291 --> 05:22.959
And I just am trying to light a fire
underneath you.

05:22.959 --> 05:25.542
Now, they have some great
motivational seminars here.

05:25.542 --> 05:27.959
I mean, one where they actually light a fire
underneath you.

05:28.375 --> 05:31.625
Okay, here's $20
for the poker machines.

05:31.625 --> 05:33.417
That's all you get. Okay?

05:33.417 --> 05:35.166
So have fun, see you in a while.

05:35.166 --> 05:37.291
- Where you going, Daddy?
- Well, I like keno.

05:37.291 --> 05:39.000
You know, you can watch sports, drink,

05:39.000 --> 05:41.917
and have an exotic woman
take your money $5 at a time.

05:41.917 --> 05:45.125
- It's like the Navy again. Hmm.
- Mm.

05:45.458 --> 05:47.083
- Come on, we're gonna be late.
- No!

05:47.083 --> 05:49.417
I am already late
starting my life, Mother.

05:49.417 --> 05:50.792
I am leaving, okay?

05:50.792 --> 05:53.458
You're gonna miss out
on the free tote bag.

05:54.458 --> 05:56.458
[CROWD CHEERING LOUDLY]

06:33.041 --> 06:36.250
MAN: Ms. Newly?
- Hi.

06:36.250 --> 06:37.542
It's been a while, ma'am.

06:38.041 --> 06:41.083
Meaning I've been here before.

06:41.083 --> 06:44.500
Meaning you probably want me to leave.
I'm really sorry.

06:44.500 --> 06:48.125
- Would you like to play?
- Oh, no. I don't have any cash on me.

06:48.125 --> 06:50.458
I could get some quarters from my mom,
but she's in a--

06:50.458 --> 06:53.709
This is in your account
from last time, $50,000.

06:55.291 --> 06:57.000
[STAMMERING]
Fifty thousand?

06:57.000 --> 06:59.083
That's--? This is my--? I could--?

06:59.083 --> 07:01.709
That's--? That's money?

07:01.709 --> 07:04.041
That's like--?

07:04.041 --> 07:06.000
I could change that-- That's mine?

07:06.000 --> 07:07.750
That's my money?

07:08.458 --> 07:10.917
You mean I could just walk away
from here with all of that?

07:10.917 --> 07:13.750
- Just free and clear?
- Yes.

07:14.458 --> 07:17.625
- Huh.
- Or you could play some.

07:21.709 --> 07:24.083
BILL: New shooter, new shooter.
Place your bet.

07:26.959 --> 07:28.333
[CROWD CHEERING AND CLAPPING]

07:29.625 --> 07:31.291
[CHUCKLES]

07:32.250 --> 07:34.291
- You wanna blow on them for good luck?
- Sure.

07:34.291 --> 07:35.750
[GIGGLES]

07:37.542 --> 07:39.500
Maybe a little.

07:39.500 --> 07:42.750
- Welcome back, Ms. Newly.
- Thanks, Bill.

07:42.750 --> 07:44.959
- It's good to be back.
- New shooter!

07:44.959 --> 07:46.125
MAN: Evening.
- Hi.

07:55.083 --> 07:58.000
Point is six, odds on the six.
Cover the hard ways.

07:58.000 --> 07:59.500
Vodka martini, dry, two olives.

07:59.500 --> 08:02.291
All right, another 500 on the come,
place the ten and 50.

08:02.291 --> 08:05.083
Come on, baby. Who likes money?

08:05.083 --> 08:06.417
[CROWD CHEERING]

08:08.041 --> 08:12.333
How do you lose $100,000?

08:12.333 --> 08:17.125
Well, first you have 50,000

08:12.333 --> 08:21.250
and you lose that.

08:17.125 --> 08:21.250
Then they lend you another 50,000

08:21.250 --> 08:23.166
That's a hundred.

08:23.166 --> 08:25.667
See, Mom? That math paid off.

08:25.667 --> 08:27.125
You're just like your mother.

08:27.125 --> 08:29.834
She lost her whole $20
while I was in the bathroom.

08:29.834 --> 08:32.208
Oh, yeah, that's gotta hurt, Dad.

08:32.583 --> 08:35.875
- Why are you smiling?
- I'm not smiling.

08:35.875 --> 08:38.458
I'm sad for you that you have to
keep working with your mother

08:38.458 --> 08:40.875
- to pay off your debt.
- That's a smile.

08:41.333 --> 08:43.583
Hmm. It's the way my mouth is set.

08:43.583 --> 08:44.959
I'm like a dolphin.

08:44.959 --> 08:47.166
No! Forget it.

08:47.166 --> 08:48.458
No, I saw it.

08:48.458 --> 08:51.959
I saw freedom and autonomy.
I had it in my hands!

08:51.959 --> 08:53.625
I know what that feels like.

08:53.625 --> 08:56.709
Daddy, were you gonna leave me anything
when you died?

08:56.709 --> 08:59.625
- Because that day is sneaking up on us.
- Oh, can't help you, kiddo.

08:59.625 --> 09:02.333
The support group I went to
after your mom's last bingo bender,

09:02.333 --> 09:04.917
it taught me the worst thing you can do
is be an enabler.

09:05.333 --> 09:06.625
Come on.

09:07.000 --> 09:09.917
- Regina! Regina. No, no.
- Just one quarter! Just one! I can feel it!

09:09.917 --> 09:11.875
- This machine, I can feel it!
- Get out of here.

09:13.166 --> 09:14.291
Here you go.

09:14.792 --> 09:16.875
How am I supposed to choke on this?
It's soft.

09:16.875 --> 09:18.667
You don't have to really choke. Pretend.

09:18.667 --> 09:21.834
Hey, I did three summers of theatre camp.
Don't question my process.

09:21.834 --> 09:22.959
[GROANS]

09:23.458 --> 09:25.083
Whew!

09:25.083 --> 09:26.291
[EXHALES]

09:26.291 --> 09:29.041
Ho, ha.

09:29.041 --> 09:30.417
All right.

09:30.750 --> 09:32.667
It's showtime.

09:32.917 --> 09:36.959
[GRUNTING]

09:36.959 --> 09:38.125
Dena!

09:38.125 --> 09:39.875
Dena, are you choking?

09:39.875 --> 09:41.709
Oh, my God, she's choking to death!

09:41.709 --> 09:44.834
It's me! Andrea Belladonna!
I'll save you!

09:44.834 --> 09:47.250
Come on. Come on, girl.

09:47.750 --> 09:50.333
Don't worry, I'm a Scout.
I know exactly what to do.

09:50.333 --> 09:53.333
- Kid, it's all right, I got it.
- No, I need my lifesaving badge.

09:53.333 --> 09:55.542
- Kid, get back!
- Ow!

09:55.542 --> 09:57.750
MAN: Oh.
- My arm!

09:57.750 --> 09:59.250
He's fine, he's fine.

09:59.250 --> 10:02.083
Andrea Belladonna broke my arm! Aah!

10:03.291 --> 10:05.625
- And scene.
- Oh.

10:06.125 --> 10:08.000
I'm just trying to help you, Bill.

10:08.000 --> 10:10.834
I mean, how can you stay in business
if people lose?

10:10.834 --> 10:13.291
You know,
that is just not a model for success.

10:13.291 --> 10:15.625
I really wish I could help you, Ms. Newly.

10:15.625 --> 10:17.208
Okay, here's the thing, Bill.

10:17.208 --> 10:19.458
I have amnesia. Yeah, yeah.

10:19.458 --> 10:22.166
You could get into a lot of trouble
for letting me play.

10:22.166 --> 10:23.625
So just give me back my money

10:23.625 --> 10:27.542
and I won't go to the
Department of Casino Rules,

10:27.542 --> 10:28.750
which is very real.

10:28.750 --> 10:31.709
- It's good to see you again, Ms. Newly.
- No, Bill! Stop. Bill.

10:31.709 --> 10:34.083
- What if I can't pay?
- I'm not worried. You'll pay.

10:34.083 --> 10:35.625
Okay, but what if I can't?

10:36.709 --> 10:39.834
- You will.
- How? Bill.

10:39.834 --> 10:41.750
They're gonna break my kneecaps,
aren't they?

10:41.750 --> 10:43.291
I need my knees, Bill.

10:43.291 --> 10:45.583
I mean,
how can I beg without my knees?

10:45.583 --> 10:48.333
Right? Bill? Bill.

10:53.834 --> 10:55.375
FUNK:
Sam?

10:58.417 --> 11:00.792
Hey, Funk.

11:00.792 --> 11:02.834
Be with you in just one second, okay?

11:02.834 --> 11:06.750
Ahem. Who makes this carpet, again?

11:09.792 --> 11:11.875
I'm gonna have to sell my apartment.

11:11.875 --> 11:13.041
I'm gonna be homeless.

11:13.041 --> 11:14.875
God, this is all my mother's fault.

11:14.875 --> 11:17.375
You know, I see homeless people
on the street and I wonder,

11:17.375 --> 11:19.917
how does something like that happen?
And you know why?

11:19.917 --> 11:21.917
They know my mom.

11:21.917 --> 11:25.583
- I know it hurts.
- Why didn't I just go to that conference?

11:26.041 --> 11:29.875
- I would have that money and a tote.
- You would have loved my seminar.

11:29.875 --> 11:32.125
I did this thing.
We lit a fire under someone's chair.

11:32.125 --> 11:34.625
Why didn't I just walk away
from that table?

11:35.834 --> 11:38.291
- Because you loved it.
- What?

11:38.291 --> 11:40.166
No, I didn't, I hated it.

11:40.166 --> 11:41.375
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

11:41.709 --> 11:43.375
Come on, the action, the buzz,

11:43.375 --> 11:46.208
money flowing in and out,
people hanging on your every move.

11:47.500 --> 11:49.458
Well, I loved that.

11:50.250 --> 11:52.125
For a moment.

11:52.333 --> 11:57.834
One sweet, ecstatic moment
of pure joy.

11:58.542 --> 12:02.208
I just-- For one moment, I was just--

12:02.917 --> 12:04.583
You were in the game.

12:04.792 --> 12:06.417
Yeah.

12:06.417 --> 12:09.375
- Come on. Come back and work for me.
- What? No.

12:09.375 --> 12:11.583
No, I'm not going backwards.

12:11.583 --> 12:14.166
Come on, I'll advance you the money.
You can work it off

12:14.166 --> 12:15.875
and leave when you want.

12:15.875 --> 12:17.875
Where's the downside here?

12:20.083 --> 12:22.000
FUNK: So you like them?
- Yes.

12:22.000 --> 12:24.792
- They make you look very attractive.
- Thank you.

12:24.792 --> 12:26.917
You're very generous to accept.

12:26.917 --> 12:30.417
Without recipients like you--
Well, just you.

12:30.417 --> 12:33.959
--the Winston Funk Foundation
would fail to keep its tax-exempt status.

12:33.959 --> 12:36.250
- Mm. They give so much.
- Mm.

12:36.250 --> 12:38.041
It makes me
wanna give something back.

12:38.041 --> 12:40.417
- Yeah? Well, I-- Mm.
- Mm.

12:43.417 --> 12:46.375
No, it's just another street corner.

12:46.375 --> 12:48.875
- No, thanks.
- All right, at least let me cover the debt.

12:48.875 --> 12:50.917
I wanna do something here to help.

12:50.917 --> 12:52.500
Oh, God, will you please stop?

12:54.041 --> 12:56.291
- Where are you going?
- I don't know.

12:56.875 --> 12:59.166
But you know what?
I'm a smart and creative woman,

12:59.166 --> 13:03.166
and I am sure there are millions of ways
for me to raise that money on my own.

13:03.917 --> 13:06.625
Sure you don't want any shoes?
I got some brand new Jimmy Choos.

13:06.625 --> 13:08.208
No, no, no.

13:08.208 --> 13:10.667
I don't come to your work
and sell my undergarments.

13:10.667 --> 13:13.208
I expect the same courtesy of you.

13:14.375 --> 13:15.875
I'll give you a free football phone.

13:17.709 --> 13:19.333
Half hour more, but that's it.

13:20.542 --> 13:24.250
Well, of course I wanted to do something
nice for young Jason here.

13:24.250 --> 13:28.709
I mean, I felt so bad after he tripped
and he broke his arm.

13:28.709 --> 13:31.333
- After you pushed me to the ground.
- Oh, you.

13:31.333 --> 13:36.000
Well, I mean, what really matters here,
as Tony Dane's fiancÃ©e, is that

13:36.000 --> 13:40.291
I was able to get a signed,
autographed basketball

13:40.291 --> 13:43.417
that I'd like to present to Jason now.

13:44.750 --> 13:48.291
<i>Thank you. You know,</i>
<i>the basketball's great and everything,</i>

13:48.291 --> 13:52.125
<i>but what I really wanna know is,</i>
<i>will you go to my prom with me?</i>

13:52.125 --> 13:53.709
<i>Oh, y--</i>

13:57.625 --> 13:59.709
<i>I'd love to.</i>

13:59.959 --> 14:01.583
Sam! Sam, come look!

14:01.583 --> 14:04.417
We have to get a new TV, because I'm
keeping that picture on this one.

14:04.709 --> 14:06.667
Ugh. That is so not fair.

14:06.667 --> 14:09.417
It's my blood,
who says I can only sell it twice a week?

14:09.417 --> 14:12.166
Well, if it helps, I could sell
some of my sports memorabilia.

14:12.166 --> 14:15.208
I have a football phone
worth a couple thousand dollars.

14:15.208 --> 14:16.417
That's okay.

14:16.417 --> 14:17.917
Don't even look for it.

14:17.917 --> 14:19.500
- Please.
- What are you gonna do?

14:19.500 --> 14:21.500
Can't raise 50 grand
selling your underwear.

14:21.500 --> 14:23.625
Well, at least not without me in it.

14:23.625 --> 14:25.625
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

14:25.625 --> 14:28.458
But it cannot involve my mother,

14:28.458 --> 14:31.709
or being taken care of by some rich guy

14:31.709 --> 14:35.208
who just wants to love me
and be with me

14:35.208 --> 14:39.041
and make everything so much easier.

14:39.041 --> 14:40.792
Wait a minute.

14:40.792 --> 14:42.792
Why don't I want that, again?

14:42.792 --> 14:45.208
- Because that won't make you happy.
- Really?

14:45.208 --> 14:46.750
Because it sounds like it would.

14:46.750 --> 14:49.250
- Sam, you're better than that.
- Maybe not.

14:49.250 --> 14:52.709
You know this. You go anywhere
near this guy, you might as well stamp

14:52.709 --> 14:54.959
"Property of Winston Funk"
all over your forehead.

14:54.959 --> 14:56.375
You'll be another acquisition.

14:56.375 --> 14:58.875
- Wait, come here, come here. Just--
- What?

14:58.875 --> 15:01.291
Look what this guy already owns.

15:01.291 --> 15:04.417
- Where on the list do you think you go?
- What are you doing on his website?

15:04.834 --> 15:07.417
I had some microwave popcorn
and the kernels didn't pop,

15:07.417 --> 15:11.542
and on the bag it said, "Division of Funk
Worldwide," so I e-mailed a complaint.

15:11.542 --> 15:13.834
Look, whatever, just look.
Dyotyne Electric?

15:13.834 --> 15:15.667
LaBasoche Champagne?

15:15.667 --> 15:17.041
- Mm-hm.
- Parkington Brand?

15:17.041 --> 15:18.834
No, no, wait.
What was that? What was that?

15:19.959 --> 15:23.250
Oh. Son of a bitch.@n

15:23.250 --> 15:25.000
He owns that casino!

15:27.792 --> 15:29.208
Seven out. Shooter loses.

15:29.750 --> 15:31.458
Oh, come on, Bill.

15:31.458 --> 15:33.959
- Let me sign for another 30.
- Cut her off, Bill.

15:33.959 --> 15:35.625
Yeah? Then you'll get cut off.

15:36.375 --> 15:38.875
- That looks like a nine from here.
- Nine pays!

15:38.875 --> 15:40.709
It does, doesn't it? Thank you.

15:41.208 --> 15:43.041
Oh, my God.

15:43.375 --> 15:46.709
He's been playing me this entire time.

15:47.041 --> 15:49.166
He lured us to that conference,

15:51.500 --> 15:55.583
put $50,000 into my account,
which I couldn't possibly have won,

15:55.792 --> 15:58.417
so then, when I lose it all,

15:58.959 --> 16:02.125
he can just show up and save the day.

16:03.500 --> 16:06.250
Flattering. Gotta give him that.

16:06.250 --> 16:09.542
And now you know
you have to stay away from him.

16:09.542 --> 16:10.875
Why?

16:10.875 --> 16:14.583
I mean, if he wants me that badly, that
just gives me leverage to get what I want.

16:15.125 --> 16:17.041
Sam, you can't beat him.

16:17.041 --> 16:19.333
You should know this by now.
The house always wins.

16:20.333 --> 16:23.875
Well, then there's only one thing
left to do.

16:23.875 --> 16:27.959
- Be the house.
- Aah.

16:35.375 --> 16:37.083
Well.

16:37.375 --> 16:39.166
Look who's been sitting in my chair.

16:39.166 --> 16:42.333
Well, I wanted to see how it blew smoke
up your butt all day long,

16:42.333 --> 16:45.000
but I can't seem to find the button.

16:45.000 --> 16:48.166
Wait a minute, I know that outfit.
If I remember, it has a tricky zipper.

16:48.625 --> 16:52.834
Well, I decided to dress up
for my job interview today.

16:52.834 --> 16:55.125
- How am I doing?
- I don't know.

16:55.125 --> 16:56.959
Where do you see yourself
in five years?

16:56.959 --> 17:00.291
Still beating you over the head
with this stapler if you don't hire me.

17:00.291 --> 17:01.959
So you want your old job back?

17:01.959 --> 17:05.125
I don't want my old job back.
I wanna run something.

17:05.125 --> 17:09.959
Something philanthropic to match
my new, more charitable reputation.

17:09.959 --> 17:12.667
- I believe we'll find a position you like.
- We always have.

17:20.250 --> 17:21.625
[GROWLS]

17:25.333 --> 17:27.166
Wow, you look beautiful.

17:27.166 --> 17:28.875
Just go.

17:28.875 --> 17:32.208
And I don't care how drunk I get,
you do not get to touch my boobs.

17:32.208 --> 17:34.458
Listen, in case we end up together,

17:34.458 --> 17:37.500
I just wanna let you know
that tricking you into this wasn't my idea.

17:37.500 --> 17:39.667
Oh, yeah, then whose idea was it?

17:41.083 --> 17:45.458
Andrea, oh, you look great!

17:45.458 --> 17:46.917
Maybe they'll vote you queen.

17:47.917 --> 17:49.667
- You.
- Me.

17:49.667 --> 17:50.875
Jason, you got my ball?

17:51.917 --> 17:55.625
God, you guys look so grown up.
Makes me wanna cry.

17:55.625 --> 17:57.250
[PRETEND-SOBS THEN LAUGHS]

17:58.041 --> 18:00.000
[MIMICS DENA'S LAUGH]

18:00.000 --> 18:02.792
Some Scout.
See if I ever buy your cookies.

18:02.792 --> 18:05.041
Look, I'm sorry. She wanted the ball,

18:05.041 --> 18:09.083
and I knew there was a chance you
wouldn't go with me if I asked straight up.

18:09.083 --> 18:13.166
You'd probably prefer the cool guys,
like in the marching band.

18:14.375 --> 18:17.291
There was a tuba player
in the tenth grade.

18:17.291 --> 18:18.458
He didn't know I was alive.

18:22.667 --> 18:25.125
Your poll numbers
came in low too, huh?

18:25.625 --> 18:26.959
Turns out being a Scout

18:26.959 --> 18:29.959
isn't exactly the chick magnet
my rabbi said it would be.

18:31.417 --> 18:34.166
What the hell? I look hot, let's go.

18:34.417 --> 18:35.625
[SIGHS]

18:35.625 --> 18:37.333
I'm not wearing that. No.

18:38.333 --> 18:39.667
[ENGINE STARTS]

18:39.959 --> 18:42.500
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

18:42.500 --> 18:45.583
Look, this shouldn't take too long,
so if you wanna get a bite afterwards,

18:45.583 --> 18:48.583
Bloody Mary's in Bora-Bora
has an amazing monkfish on Friday.

18:48.583 --> 18:52.375
Mm. That sounds good.
Let me just do this first, okay?

18:52.375 --> 18:53.875
- Right.
- Yeah.

19:02.458 --> 19:05.250
- Ladies and gentlemen of the press.
- Uh, uh-- No. Save it.

19:05.250 --> 19:07.500
- That's sensitive.
- I-- Oh, okay. I'm sorry.

19:07.500 --> 19:09.333
Sorry about that.

19:09.333 --> 19:12.542
- Do I--? Okay, okay.
- Just about-- From, like, yeah.

19:12.542 --> 19:14.959
Ladies and gentlemen
of the business press,

19:14.959 --> 19:16.583
I am Samantha Newly,

19:16.583 --> 19:19.500
Vice President
of the Winston Funk Foundation.

19:19.500 --> 19:21.834
Today is a great day,

19:21.834 --> 19:24.709
because although the foundation
has fallen short

19:24.709 --> 19:27.834
of its giving goals in recent years,

19:27.834 --> 19:32.000
today, Mr. Funk is pledging

19:32.375 --> 19:38.041
$30 million a year to various charities
at my sole discretion.

19:38.959 --> 19:41.291
I'm sure Mr. Funk and I
will make fine partners,

19:41.291 --> 19:45.875
because he told me personally,
all he wants to do is help.

19:46.625 --> 19:50.458
Now, Mr. Funk will answer
all of your questions.

19:51.333 --> 19:55.166
I'm gonna take a rain check on that lunch,
because I'm gonna be awfully busy.

19:55.166 --> 19:56.667
Okay.

19:57.166 --> 19:59.709
Mr. Funk, excuse me,
I was just curious--

19:59.709 --> 20:03.083
SAM: <i>You know, just because your life</i>
<i>is already pretty far down one road,</i>

20:03.083 --> 20:05.125
<i>doesn't mean you can't take a detour.</i>

20:05.125 --> 20:06.375
Hey, Mom!

20:06.375 --> 20:08.291
I'm returning your arrow!

20:08.291 --> 20:12.291
I can't have it at my place.
I keep making a wrong turn at the kitchen.

20:12.291 --> 20:14.417
- Guess what!
- What?

20:14.417 --> 20:16.625
I sold a house!

20:16.959 --> 20:21.125
Oh. Whoa. Sorry, I didn't hear you.
All I heard was "Chardonnay."

20:21.125 --> 20:23.125
- What happened?
- They told us at that seminar

20:23.125 --> 20:25.583
that we had to find our motivation,

20:25.583 --> 20:29.125
and my disappointment in you
was the only motivation I needed,

20:29.125 --> 20:33.542
so as long as you keep letting me down,
there's gonna be no stopping me.

20:35.500 --> 20:37.709
<i>Don't worry if there's no sign</i>
<i>to point the way.</i>

20:37.709 --> 20:40.917
<i>Just trust your own compass</i>
<i>and follow the arrow.</i>

20:40.917 --> 20:42.917
[UKULELE PLAYING]

20:42.917 --> 20:45.625
<i>The point is to take the wheel</i>
<i>and drive.</i>

20:45.625 --> 20:49.458
<i>Sometimes the side roads</i>
<i>are where you find the best surprises.</i>

20:50.125 --> 20:54.667
Hey. You know, it's hard to play
the ukulele without looking like a dork,

20:54.667 --> 20:56.625
but you keep at it.

20:58.625 --> 21:01.417
So you wanna go out
on Saturday night?

21:04.458 --> 21:05.500
Yes.

21:09.500 --> 21:10.709
<i>It's a game, right?</i>

21:10.709 --> 21:13.458
<i>I mean, you can't win if you don't play.</i>
